{"id":"1612.03954","submitter":"Gregory Schehr","authors":"David S. Dean, Pierre Le Doussal, Satya N. Majumdar, Gregory Schehr","title":"Statistics of the maximal distance and momentum in a trapped Fermi gas\n  at low temperature","comments":"28 pages, 4 figures","journal-ref":"J. Stat. Mech. (2017) 063301","doi":"10.1088/1742-5468/aa6dda","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.stat-mech cond-mat.quant-gas math-ph math.MP math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We consider $N$ non-interacting fermions in an isotropic $d$-dimensional\nharmonic trap. We compute analytically the cumulative distribution of the\nmaximal radial distance of the fermions from the trap center at zero\ntemperature. While in $d=1$ the limiting distribution (in the large $N$ limit),\nproperly centered and scaled, converges to the squared Tracy-Widom distribution\nof the Gaussian Unitary Ensemble in Random Matrix Theory, we show that for all\n$d>1$, the limiting distribution converges to the Gumbel law. These limiting\nforms turn out to be universal, i.e., independent of the details of the\ntrapping potential for a large class of isotropic trapping potentials. We also\nstudy the position of the right-most fermion in a given direction in $d$\ndimensions and, in the case of a harmonic trap, the maximum momentum, and show\nthat they obey similar Gumbel statistics. Finally, we generalize these results\nto low but finite temperature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Dec 2016 22:28:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-06-12"}
