in the wave equations is inferred from the GS model. The overall goal\nis to show that fractional calculus is not just a mathematical framework which\ncan be used to curve-fit the complex behavior of materials. Rather, it can also\nbe derived from real physical processes as illustrated in this work by the\nexample of grain-shearing.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Dec 2016 15:43:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 Dec 2016 05:53:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-01"}
